your boobies.

01:31.149 --> 01:33.150
Well, I don't wave
to the guy at the record shop

01:33.152 --> 01:34.368
that you had sex with.

01:34.370 --> 01:37.703
I had sex with the guy
at the record shop?

01:38.624 --> 01:40.374
I should keep a diary.

01:40.376 --> 01:42.326
Oh, God, he's coming back.

01:42.328 --> 01:43.911
See what you started with your wave?

01:43.913 --> 01:46.196
I'm sorry.
My hand is friendly.

01:46.198 --> 01:48.716
Ask any guy in high school.

01:49.218 --> 01:51.018
I was gonna try and sneak by,

01:51.020 --> 01:53.337
but that just seemed
so juvenile, so here...

01:54.339 --> 01:55.539
"Do you guys still like me?

01:55.541 --> 01:58.874
"Check 'Yes' or 'No.'"

01:59.211 --> 02:00.478
So how's she doing?

02:00.480 --> 02:02.713
- She's good.
- Really?

02:03.215 --> 02:06.048
Oh, by the way, the guy
at the record store says hi.

02:06.752 --> 02:09.485
Well, you tell him
I said, "who are you?"

02:12.224 --> 02:13.808
And I also came in because
I wanted to make sure

02:13.810 --> 02:15.225
everything's cool with you and me, Max.

02:15.227 --> 02:17.027
I mean, you haven't texted me a pic

02:17.029 --> 02:19.229
of an unlikely animal friendship
in, like, 48 hours.

02:19.231 --> 02:21.198
Don't worry, we're cool.
I just haven't been able

02:21.200 --> 02:22.783
to top the picture I sent of the monkey

02:22.785 --> 02:25.002
tickling a parrot.

02:25.004 --> 02:26.504
I get it.
You have high standards.

02:26.506 --> 02:28.906
Whereas, me, I see a black dog
spooning a brown dog,

02:28.908 --> 02:30.541
and I pull the trigger.

02:30.543 --> 02:32.710
Well, save that amateur crap
for your mom,

02:32.712 --> 02:34.912
perhaps with an aunt and uncle CC.

02:34.914 --> 02:36.630
Ha, that is so me.

02:36.632 --> 02:38.382
Well, sir, you have raised the bar.

02:38.384 --> 02:41.717
I look forward to our next
freaky/adorable animal pic.

02:43.222 --> 02:45.222
Well, are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

02:45.224 --> 02:48.557
Since we broke up, he got fat.

02:49.762 --> 02:52.095
It's only been four days.

02:52.097 --> 02:54.815
Wynonna Judd gets fat in an hour.

02:55.717 --> 02:57.935
I'm too exhausted
to even think about Andy.

02:57.937 --> 03:00.237
Let's just change and get to the diner.

03:00.239 --> 03:01.322
Look, all we have to do is make it

03:01.324 --> 03:02.456
through eight more hours,

03:02.458 --> 03:05.709
and then we can get
a good night's sleep.

03:05.711 --> 03:08.946
Max, you're taking
your pants off in public!

03:08.948 --> 03:10.714
Oh, my God!

03:10.716 --> 03:14.049
I'm so tired, I forgot where I was!

03:14.387 --> 03:17.104
They're halfway down.
What do I do?

03:17.606 --> 03:20.439
I'm too tired to make the call.

03:24.062 --> 03:27.395
And I'll have the BLT
with the French fries.

03:27.396 --> 03:30.649
Miss? I think our waitress
is asleep.

03:31.821 --> 03:33.404
Yeah, she's tired.
We haven't slept a lot lately.

03:33.406 --> 03:34.888
When she wakes up,
she'll take your order.

03:34.890 --> 03:37.024
- But we're really hungry--
- Leave her alone!

03:37.026 --> 03:40.344
So I come to your job and wake you up?

03:40.596 --> 03:43.113
Hi, can I take your order?

03:43.115 --> 03:45.666
I can see how tired you are, Max.

03:45.668 --> 03:48.318
And if I could turn the clock
back to '75,

03:48.320 --> 03:51.653
I'd help you out
with a nice bump of cocaine.

03:51.824 --> 03:53.457
But I don't do that anymore.

03:53.459 --> 03:55.993
Earl, you quit coke in 1975?

03:55.995 --> 03:59.328
No, when I was 75, last year.

03:59.715 --> 04:03.048
It just felt like time.

04:03.135 --> 04:06.468
Now all I can give you is
a nice bump of this.

04:07.106 --> 04:09.290
Max, I need you
to explain something to me

04:09.292 --> 04:10.674
'cause I can't figure it out.

04:10.676 --> 04:14.009
That's hard to believe,
since you're 90% head.

04:14.814 --> 04:16.480
It's not a laughing matter, Max.

04:16.482 --> 04:19.815
I broke my mother's pelvis coming out.

04:23.038 --> 04:26.371
At least you finally came out.

04:28.359 --> 04:30.878
Oh, so you're awake enough
to ridicule the boss,

04:30.880 --> 04:32.796
but not awake enough to wait on tables.

04:32.798 --> 04:36.131
Exactly. See,
there's that big head working.

04:36.385 --> 04:37.835
And don't exaggerate.

04:37.837 --> 04:39.970
Caroline and I are doing a great job.

04:39.972 --> 04:43.305
- Wake up.
- Hi, can I take your order?

04:43.726 --> 04:45.759
All I knows is.
if I was doing my job

04:45.761 --> 04:48.512
as bad as you two tonight,
I'd take my own life.

04:48.514 --> 04:51.847
That's not off the table.

04:52.384 --> 04:53.701
Come on, Han, cut us a break.

04:53.703 --> 04:55.986
We're working two jobs,
we got two hours of sleep.

04:55.988 --> 04:58.188
We just want to get home
and climb into bed.

04:58.190 --> 05:01.523
You're sleeping together?

05:01.777 --> 05:05.110
I mean, it's been a "will they
or won't they" since they met.

05:07.916 --> 05:10.584
Hi, everybody.
Sophie's here!

05:10.586 --> 05:13.919
And look at my new coat.
It's double-breasted.

05:15.508 --> 05:18.392
Pretty nice, huh?
It was a gift from me.

05:18.394 --> 05:20.077
It's the only thing he ever gave me

05:20.079 --> 05:23.412
that didn't threaten
my reproductive health.

05:23.883 --> 05:25.683
Think that fox took its own life

05:25.685 --> 05:28.519
when it saw what kind of coat
it was gonna be on.

05:28.521 --> 05:30.187
What is the occasion?

05:30.189 --> 05:33.522
What is the occasion?
I'm hot and it's cold.

05:34.926 --> 05:37.644
And it's also the anniversary
of the first time

05:37.646 --> 05:39.980
Oleg and I 70ed.

05:39.982 --> 05:43.315
The way I do it, it's one more than 69.

05:48.990 --> 05:51.959
Max, I just hung up
from a very panicked phone call,

05:51.961 --> 05:53.794
and you'll never believe what happened.

05:53.796 --> 05:55.412
The guy from the record store
called to say

05:55.414 --> 05:57.998
I have super gonorrhea?

05:59.000 --> 06:01.333
You actually think a guy
that you don't even remember

06:01.721 --> 06:05.054
called to tell me
that you have super gonorrhea?

06:06.074 --> 06:08.926
Yes, that's how tired I am.

06:08.928 --> 06:11.729
Are you gonna make me wait
forever? Do I have it or not?

06:11.731 --> 06:15.064
It's not super gonorrhea,
but it is super-bad news.

06:15.401 --> 06:17.151
This woman just called
to confirm her order

06:17.153 --> 06:19.069
for 1,000 cupcakes for tomorrow.

06:19.071 --> 06:21.638
I've been so tired,
I completely forgot.

06:21.640 --> 06:24.973
I'd rather have super gonorrhea!

06:25.161 --> 06:28.245
Are you insane? We can't do
1,000 cupcakes by tomorrow.

06:28.247 --> 06:29.479
We <i>have</i> to do it.

06:29.481 --> 06:31.448
It'll ruin our reputation if we don't.

06:31.450 --> 06:33.867
I know we're tired,
but if we stay up all night,

06:33.869 --> 06:36.820
we'll have $4,000
by tomorrow at 10:00 a.m.

06:36.822 --> 06:38.822
They have to be done
by 10:00 a.m.?

06:38.824 --> 06:42.157
I'm so tired, remind me--
Is a.m. the morning one?

06:42.995 --> 06:44.711
We can't do it.
It's impossible.

06:44.713 --> 06:46.680
My brain's too foggy
to crunch the numbers,

06:46.682 --> 06:48.766
but I'm sure it's doable
if we leave right now.

06:48.768 --> 06:50.434
We're in the middle of waiting tables.

06:50.436 --> 06:52.519
Well, we'll just have to
come up with an excuse.

06:52.521 --> 06:55.522
Give me your hand, bend over,
and pretend to be sick.

06:55.524 --> 06:58.008
It'll work. I've used this
to get out of eight jobs,

06:58.010 --> 07:01.343
six final exams, and one wedding.

07:01.981 --> 07:03.831
Han, we have an emergency.
Caroline's sick.

07:03.833 --> 07:06.016
She's so sick, she can't even stand up.

07:06.018 --> 07:07.651
We won't be able to stay
and finish our shift.

07:07.653 --> 07:09.153
We have to go right
to the emergency room.

07:10.856 --> 07:12.456
We don't know what's wrong with her,

07:12.458 --> 07:13.523
but it's coming out of both ends.

07:13.525 --> 07:15.375
It might be super gonorrhea.
Bye.

07:20.464 --> 07:22.365
That's so unfortunate.

07:22.367 --> 07:25.700
