Andy just sent me a picture
of a deer nursing a turtle.

08:16.774 --> 08:18.857
This is why they tell teen turtles

08:18.859 --> 08:20.742
never to post up on Facebook.

08:20.744 --> 08:24.077
Oh, I didn't realize
you two were still texting.

08:24.164 --> 08:25.781
Well, we're mostly
just sending pictures

08:25.783 --> 08:27.565
of unlikely animal friendships.

08:27.567 --> 08:29.785
See, there's a bear napping
with a bunny.

08:29.787 --> 08:31.203
And what's this?

08:31.205 --> 08:33.087
It's a labradoodle
high-fiving a koi fish.

08:33.090 --> 08:34.673
It's pretty self-explanatory.

08:34.674 --> 08:37.876
No, underneath that.
This-- "How's Caroline?"

08:37.878 --> 08:40.379
I thought this was just
an unlikely animal friendship.

08:40.381 --> 08:42.746
It is, mostly, but every other text,

08:42.749 --> 08:44.883
I get the idea that
maybe he's not over you.

08:45.285 --> 08:47.519
He's the one who broke up with <i>me.</i>

08:47.521 --> 08:49.554
Well, maybe he regrets it.

08:49.556 --> 08:52.057
Maybe you two are like
Chris Brown and Rihanna,

08:52.059 --> 08:54.643
minus the punching and the duet.

08:55.345 --> 08:56.528
I'm kind of surprised.

08:56.530 --> 08:58.563
I thought you guys were good together.

08:58.565 --> 09:01.149
