13:54.413 --> 13:55.979
Well, if they're in love,

13:55.981 --> 13:57.697
it's really none of your business.

13:57.699 --> 14:00.533
Why are you texting him
in the middle of the night?

14:00.535 --> 14:03.570
In fact, why is he still up?
Is he talking about me?

14:03.572 --> 14:04.487
You look upset.

14:04.489 --> 14:05.789
Do you want me to stop texting him?

14:05.791 --> 14:08.541
No. It's fine.
It's just I'm tired

14:08.543 --> 14:10.410
and we're almost finished,
and I just wanna go home.

14:10.812 --> 14:12.712
Got it.
I'm so hot.

14:12.714 --> 14:15.048
Let me just get this hair off my neck.

14:15.550 --> 14:17.784
Max, why are you wearing
only one earring?

14:17.786 --> 14:20.136
What are you talking about?
I'm wearing two.

14:20.138 --> 14:23.456
That's weird. Where is it?
Is it in my hair?

14:23.758 --> 14:25.958
- No, no.
- Did it fall down?

14:25.960 --> 14:27.010
Yeah, check your boobs.

14:27.012 --> 14:29.813
That's where you found the remote.

14:29.815 --> 14:32.348
It's not--
it's not anywhere on me.

14:32.350 --> 14:33.800
Well, when's the last time you saw it?

14:33.802 --> 14:35.568
I don't know,
but it couldn't have gone far.

14:35.570 --> 14:37.937
I was in this area
pretty much the whole night.

14:37.939 --> 14:41.272
You mean over the batter?

14:42.143 --> 14:44.143
No, no, no.
Nothing, nothing, nothing!

14:44.145 --> 14:45.495
No, no, no, no, nothing,
nothing, nothing!

14:45.497 --> 14:47.447
No, no, no, no, no!
Nothing, nothing, no!

14:47.449 --> 14:49.499
It's not here, which means

14:49.501 --> 14:51.785
it's in one of those
already-baked cupcakes.

14:51.787 --> 14:55.120
Let's go. We have to start
pulling these apart.

14:55.240 --> 14:57.373
Really? Come on,
don't be ridiculous.

14:57.375 --> 15:00.093
Look, worst-case scenario,
one of the 1,000 cupcakes

15:00.095 --> 15:01.261
has an earring in it.

15:01.263 --> 15:03.379
We'll tell them it's a surprise.

15:03.381 --> 15:06.433
No, the worst-case scenario
is someone bites into it,

15:06.435 --> 15:08.802
rips their lip open, and sues us.

15:08.804 --> 15:11.170
Let them sue us.
We don't have any money.

15:11.172 --> 15:12.856
And that's why we'll go to jail.

15:12.858 --> 15:14.340
Yep, I'll be locked up raw

15:14.342 --> 15:15.859
and forced to be someone's girlfriend.

15:15.861 --> 15:17.444
I mean, I'm a bad girlfriend
out of prison.

15:17.446 --> 15:19.679
It's not gonna be any easier
with big Joan.

15:19.681 --> 15:23.014
Calm down. If we go to prison,
I'll be your girlfriend.

15:23.151 --> 15:24.617
Until someone hotter comes along,

15:24.619 --> 15:26.519
'cause that's the way it goes
in prison.

15:26.521 --> 15:27.871
Start looking.

15:27.873 --> 15:30.824
I am not going to smash 900 cupcakes.

15:30.826 --> 15:32.625
Then we'll just have to start over.

15:32.627 --> 15:35.712
Oh, no, I would rather
hitch a ride West

15:35.714 --> 15:38.030
and become a sister-wife.

15:40.334 --> 15:42.218
This is crazy.
Can't I just text them

15:42.220 --> 15:43.803
and tell them we can't do the job?

15:43.805 --> 15:46.539
No, you can't text them.
We need the money.

15:46.541 --> 15:48.207
And stop with all the texting.

15:48.209 --> 15:49.976
Maybe if you were thinking less
about texting

15:49.978 --> 15:51.344
with my ex-boyfriend,

15:51.346 --> 15:53.763
you wouldn't have lost
your earring in the first place.

15:53.765 --> 15:55.181
You should have just said it.

15:55.183 --> 15:57.684
You have a problem
with me texting Andy.

15:57.686 --> 16:00.019
I do not have a problem with it!

16:00.021 --> 16:02.221
Oh, good, 'cause he's my friend too.

16:02.223 --> 16:04.574
You'd think your loyalty
to your best friend

16:04.576 --> 16:06.392
and business partner
would be more important

16:06.394 --> 16:08.528
than some stupid animal friendship!

16:08.530 --> 16:10.330
I mean...

16:10.332 --> 16:12.031
I'm surprised I even have
to tell you that, Max.

16:12.033 --> 16:13.199
It's kind of girl code.

16:13.201 --> 16:16.534
Oh, I am way to tired
to hear "girl code."

16:17.172 --> 16:19.889
Shut it down.

16:19.891 --> 16:23.224
Girl code, Max.
Girl code.

16:25.096 --> 16:28.429
Shut up, Caroline.
Shut up!

16:30.251 --> 16:32.936
I'm not even gonna
dignify that with a response.

16:32.938 --> 16:35.305
Yeah, that was the goal, bitch.

16:35.807 --> 16:37.390
I don't have time for this.

16:37.392 --> 16:39.225
I have to find an earring that you lost

16:39.227 --> 16:41.427
in one of these
thousand cupcakes, bitch!

16:42.379 --> 16:45.962
The thousand cupcakes that
you forgot to tell me about!

16:47.101 --> 16:49.536
And the girl code
means that when a girl

16:49.538 --> 16:50.853
breaks up with someone,

16:50.855 --> 16:52.422
you don't interfere
with their boyfriend,

16:52.424 --> 16:54.924
because she needs some distance!

16:54.926 --> 16:56.776
Well, why didn't you tell me that

16:56.778 --> 17:00.111
when I asked you 14 hours ago?

17:01.632 --> 17:03.965
Hey, Max.
I got your text.

17:04.169 --> 17:06.051
I'm here to help.

17:06.554 --> 17:09.387
Um, that was
a pre-girl-code text.

17:11.509 --> 17:13.092
I thought we maybe needed a backup

17:13.094 --> 17:16.127
after Earl passed up
and I made Han cry.

17:21.285 --> 17:24.367
Andy, on the list of things
I feel guilty about in life,

17:24.806 --> 17:26.489
calling you to help
in the middle of the night

17:26.491 --> 17:27.607
is number two.

17:27.608 --> 17:28.741
It would be number one if I hadn't

17:28.743 --> 17:29.909
pushed that girl down the stairs

17:29.911 --> 17:32.478
to get into the 98 Degrees
concert before her.

17:32.480 --> 17:35.813
Well, it was 98 Degrees.
People had to die.

17:37.919 --> 17:39.586
Okay, let's stop
all this joking and get down

17:39.588 --> 17:40.787
to why I really came here.

17:40.789 --> 17:42.589
Come on, Caroline, love me.

17:43.091 --> 17:45.491
Did you just say, "Caroline, love me"?

17:45.493 --> 17:47.594
No, I said,
"Caroline, glove me."

17:47.596 --> 17:48.761
What kind of loser would say,

17:48.763 --> 17:52.096
"love me"?
Unless you do.

17:55.686 --> 17:57.103
So how you doing?

17:57.105 --> 18:00.438
I'm okay.
A little tired.

18:00.675 --> 18:03.059
You know, I've been
thinking about you a lot.

18:03.061 --> 18:05.528
Pretty much all the time
since we broke up.

18:05.530 --> 18:08.114
Um, maybe I overreacted to your whole

18:08.116 --> 18:10.349
obsession with work thing, you know?

18:10.751 --> 18:12.619
- Well, you are here
at 4:00 a.m.

18:12.621 --> 18:15.488
'Cause I needed help making
1,000 cupcakes in four hours.

18:15.490 --> 18:17.457
One might call that obsessive.

18:17.759 --> 18:20.792
One might.
Or pretty much everyone might.

18:21.713 --> 18:25.046
And, Andy, just know that
even though it didn't work out,

18:26.751 --> 18:29.919
I do <i>glove</i> you.

18:29.921 --> 18:32.088
I glove you too.

18:32.590 --> 18:34.641
Now, get the cupcakes out
before they burn.

18:34.643 --> 18:36.375
I don't have the energy
to do this all again.

18:36.377 --> 18:39.710
Ah, there's the girl I broke up with.

18:39.881 --> 18:41.764
Everything's ready to go out there.

18:41.766 --> 18:43.266
I've had my hands in more boxes tonight

18:43.268 --> 18:46.436
than a gynecologist at a free clinic.

18:50.525 --> 18:52.391
It's not <i>that</i> funny.

18:52.393 --> 18:54.327
Stay up another 27 hours,

18:54.329 --> 18:56.579
it'll be the funniest damn thing
you ever heard.

18:59.250 --> 19:00.867
Well, that's the end of it.

19:00.869 --> 19:02.401
Yeah, I think it is.

19:02.403 --> 19:04.871
Max, I'm talking about more
than the cupcakes.

19:04.873 --> 19:08.206
Yeah, I could tell
by your Bradley Cooper tone.

19:08.209 --> 19:10.076
So what, it's not gonna work out
between you two?

19:10.078 --> 19:12.762
No. And I think
we have to break up.

19:12.764 --> 19:14.213
I thought you already broke up.

19:14.215 --> 19:16.082
No, I'm talking about you and me.

19:16.084 --> 19:17.884
You're dumping <i>me?</i>

19:17.886 --> 19:19.352
Wow, last guy who dumped me,

19:19.354 --> 19:21.804
I burned down his house and moved.

19:21.806 --> 19:23.923
Still wanna continue this conversation?

19:23.925 --> 19:25.224
Max, it wouldn't work.

19:25.226 --> 19:27.093
I would always be asking you
about Caroline.

19:27.095 --> 19:28.778
Look, I get it, it's weird.

19:28.780 --> 19:31.230
People don't usually stay
friends with their friend's ex,

19:31.232 --> 19:34.565
but then, cats don't usually
become friends with dolphins.

19:35.453 --> 19:38.604
But sometimes, for no
apparent reason, it happens.

19:38.606 --> 19:40.540
Yeah, I just wish I was as grown up

19:40.542 --> 19:42.408
as a cat or a dolphin.

19:42.410 --> 19:44.293
I hear ya.

19:44.295 --> 19:45.962
So what's next, breakup text?

19:45.964 --> 19:48.164
Nah, that's just gonna lead
to makeup text,

19:48.166 --> 19:50.717
and then we're back in a vicious cycle.

19:51.119 --> 19:52.618
All right, I'll just
stop by your place,

19:52.620 --> 19:54.003
pick up my CDs,
my T-shirts,

19:54.005 --> 19:55.421
and the 3 grand I left there.

19:55.423 --> 19:57.090
Max, you've never been to my place.

19:57.092 --> 19:59.175
See, this is why
I'm breaking up with you--

19:59.177 --> 20:01.144
you're a liar.

20:01.146 --> 20:03.629
See you in small claims court, bub.

20:06.466 --> 20:09.799
Well, we did it, Max.
We made $4,000.

20:10.905 --> 20:12.939
And as far as Andy and I go,

20:12.941 --> 20:14.290
I think we're in the right place,

20:14.292 --> 20:16.075
because when he said
he'd been thinking about me

20:16.077 --> 20:17.476
since the breakup,

20:17.478 --> 20:19.695
I realized I'd only been
thinking about the cupcakes.

20:19.697 --> 20:22.665
Oh, please, God, shut up.

20:22.667 --> 20:24.834
Thank you.
I was dying to shut up.

20:24.836 --> 20:27.954
Ooh.

20:27.956 --> 20:30.339
Look, it's a text from the place.

20:30.341 --> 20:32.959
They loved the cupcakes.

20:32.961 --> 20:34.961
Wait, why do I have my phone
in your apron?

20:34.963 --> 20:37.713
No, my phone was in my apron.

20:37.715 --> 20:40.016
Unless I handed you the wrong apron

20:40.018 --> 20:42.518
after I wiped them down.

20:42.520 --> 20:45.538
What? <i>What?</i>

20:45.540 --> 20:48.775
Oh... Your earring.

20:48.777 --> 20:50.693
I had it in there the whole time.

20:50.695 --> 20:52.645
Oh, we're idiots!

20:52.647 --> 20:55.980
We're two very different kinds
of idiots, but we're idiots.

20:56.534 --> 20:58.651
And yet, somehow we work.

20:58.653 --> 21:00.653
We're the most unlikely animal friends.

21:00.655 --> 21:03.156
I don't know about that,
but a picture of me nursing you

21:03.158 --> 21:05.491
would definitely go viral.

21:05.493 --> 21:08.444
- Good night.
- Good night.

21:08.446 --> 21:09.545
Where you going?

21:09.547 --> 21:10.797
I'm too tired to pull my bed down.

21:10.799 --> 21:12.715
- I'm sleeping with you.
- No, you're not.

21:12.717 --> 21:14.967
You have super gonorrhea.

